Description: Body sherd of Attic black-figured pottery amphora; exterior: undetermined scene; from left, added red area (directly on ground) with incised black area on its right (female drapery?); black area with rosette of white dots around red core, and some short red lines obscured by a splodge of red.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.0066) (Phase 1)
